name: Loop
definitions: A collection of connected equipment; part of a System

name: Air_Loop
definitions: The set of connected equipment serving one path of air

name: Water_Loop
definitions: A collection of equipment that transport and regulate water among each other

name: Chilled_Water_Loop
definitions: A collection of equipment that transport and regulate chilled water among each other

name: Hot_Water_Loop
definitions: A collection of equipment that transport and regulate hot water among each other

name: PV_Array
definitions: A collection of photovoltaic panels

name: Photovoltaic_Array
definitions: A collection of photovoltaic panels

name: Portfolio
definitions: A collection of sites

name: System
definitions: A System is a combination of equipment and auxiliary devices (e.g., controls, accessories, interconnecting means, and termi­nal elements) by which energy is transformed so it performs a specific function such as HVAC, service water heating, or lighting. (ASHRAE Dictionary).

name: Domestic_Hot_Water_System
definitions: The equipment, devices and conduits that handle the production and distribution of domestic hot water in a building

name: Electrical_System
definitions: Devices that serve or are part of the electrical subsystem in the building

name: Energy_System
definitions: A collection of devices that generates, stores or transports electricity

name: Energy_Generation_System
definitions: A collection of devices that generates electricity

name: PV_Generation_System
definitions: A collection of photovoltaic devices that generates energy

name: Energy_Storage_System
definitions: A collection of devices that stores electricity

name: Battery_Energy_Storage_System
definitions: A collection of batteries that provides energy storage, along with their supporting equipment

name: HVAC_System
definitions: See Heating_Ventilation_Air_Conditioning_System
The equipment, distribution systems and terminals that provide, either collectively or individually, the processes of heating, ventilating or air conditioning to a building or portion of a building

name: Heating_Ventilation_Air_Conditioning_System
definitions: The equipment, distribution systems and terminals that provide, either collectively or individually, the processes of heating, ventilating or air conditioning to a building or portion of a building
See Heating_Ventilation_Air_Conditioning_System

name: Air_System
definitions: The equipment, distribution systems and terminals that introduce or exhaust, either collectively or individually, the air into and from the building

name: Ventilation_Air_System
definitions: The equipment, devices, and conduits that handle the introduction and distribution of ventilation air in the building
The equipment, distribution systems and terminals that introduce or exhaust, either collectively or individually, the air used for the ventilation system of the building

name: Steam_System
definitions: The equipment, devices and conduits that handle the production and distribution of steam in a building

name: Water_System
definitions: The equipment, devices and conduits that handle the production and distribution of water in a building

name: Chilled_Water_System
definitions: The equipment, devices and conduits that handle the production and distribution of chilled water in a building

name: Condenser_Water_System
definitions: A heat rejection system consisting of (typically) cooling towers, condenser water pumps, chillers and the piping connecting the components

name: Hot_Water_System
definitions: The equipment, devices and conduits that handle the production and distribution of hot water in a building

name: Lighting_System
definitions: The equipment, devices and interfaces that serve or are a part of the lighting subsystem in a building

name: Emergency_Power_Off_System
definitions: A system that can power down a single piece of equipment or a single system from a single point

name: Fire_Safety_System
definitions: A system containing devices and equipment that monitor, detect and suppress fire hazards

name: Shading_System
definitions: Devices that can control daylighting through various means

name: Equipment
definitions: devices that serve all or part of the building and may include electric power, lighting, transportation, or service water heating, including, but not limited to, furnaces, boilers, air conditioners, heat pumps, chillers, water heaters, lamps, luminaires, ballasts, elevators, escalators, or other devices or installations.

name: Breaker_Panel
definitions: Breaker Panel distributes power into various end-uses.

name: Bus_Riser
definitions: Bus Risers are commonly fed from a switchgear and rise up through a series of floors to the main power distribution source for each floor.

name: Disconnect_Switch
definitions: Building power is most commonly provided by utility company through a master disconnect switch (sometimes called a service disconnect) in the main electrical room of a building. The Utility Company provided master disconnect switch often owns or restricts access to this switch. There can also be other cases where a disconnect is placed into an electrical system to allow service cut-off to a portion of the building.

name: Energy_Storage
definitions: Devices or equipment that store energy in its various forms

name: Battery
definitions: A container that stores chemical energy that can be converted into electricity and used as a source of power

name: Inverter
definitions: A device that changes direct current into alternating current

name: Motor_Control_Center
definitions: The Motor Control Center is a specialized type of switchgear which provides electrical power to major mechanical systems in the building such as HVAC components.

name: PlugStrip
definitions: A device containing a block of electrical sockets allowing multiple electrical devices to be powered from a single electrical socket.

name: Switchgear
definitions: A main disconnect or service disconnect feeds power to a switchgear, which then distributes power to the rest of the building through smaller amperage-rated disconnects.

name: Transformer
definitions: A Transformer is usually fed by a high-voltage source and then steps down the voltage to a lower-voltage feed for low-voltage application (such as lights). Transformers also can step up voltage, but this generally does not apply to in building distribution.

name: Elevator
definitions: A device that provides vertical transportation between floors, levels or decks of a building, vessel or other structure

name: Fire_Control_Panel
definitions: A panel-mounted device that provides status and control of a fire safety system

name: Furniture
definitions: Movable objects intended to support various human activities such as seating, eating and sleeping

name: Stage_Riser
definitions: A low platform in a space or on a stage

name: Gas_Distribution
definitions: Utilize a gas distribution source to represent how gas is distributed across multiple destinations

name: HVAC_Equipment
definitions: See Heating_Ventilation_Air_Conditioning_System

name: AHU
definitions: Assembly consisting of sections containing a fan or fans and other necessary equipment to perform one or more of the following functions: circulating, filtration, heating, cooling, heat recovery, humidifying, dehumidifying, and mixing of air. Is usually connected to an air-distribution system.

name: DOAS
definitions: See Dedicated_Outdoor_Air_System_Unit

A device that conditions and delivers 100% outdoor air to its assigned spaces. It decouples air-conditioning of the outdoor air, usually used to provide minimum outdoor air ventilation, from conditioning of the internal loads.

name: Dedicated_Outdoor_Air_System_Unit
definitions: A device that conditions and delivers 100% outdoor air to its assigned spaces. It decouples air-conditioning of the outdoor air, usually used to provide minimum outdoor air ventilation, from conditioning of the internal loads.
See Dedicated_Outdoor_Air_System_Unit

name: MAU
definitions: See Makeup_Air_Unit

A device designed to condition ventilation air introduced into a space or to replace air exhausted from a process or general area exhaust. The device may be used to prevent negative pressure within buildings or to reduce airborne contaminants in a space.

name: Makeup_Air_Unit
definitions: A device designed to condition ventilation air introduced into a space or to replace air exhausted from a process or general area exhaust. The device may be used to prevent negative pressure within buildings or to reduce airborne contaminants in a space.
See Makeup_Air_Unit

name: PAU
definitions: A type of AHU, use to pre-treat the outdoor air before feed to AHU

name: RTU
definitions: see Rooftop_Unit
Packaged air conditioner mounted on a roof, the conditioned air being discharged directly into the rooms below or through a duct system.

name: Rooftop_Unit
definitions: Packaged air conditioner mounted on a roof, the conditioned air being discharged directly into the rooms below or through a duct system.
see Rooftop_Unit

name: Air_Handler_Unit
definitions: Assembly consisting of sections containing a fan or fans and other necessary equipment to perform one or more of the following functions: circulating, filtration, heating, cooling, heat recovery, humidifying, dehumidifying, and mixing of air. Is usually connected to an air-distribution system.

name: Air_Handling_Unit
definitions: Assembly consisting of sections containing a fan or fans and other necessary equipment to perform one or more of the following functions: circulating, filtration, heating, cooling, heat recovery, humidifying, dehumidifying, and mixing of air. Is usually connected to an air-distribution system.

name: Air_Plenum
definitions: A component of the HVAC the receives air from the air handling unit or room to distribute or exhaust to or from the building

name: Return_Air_Plenum
definitions: A component of the HVAC the receives air from the room to recirculate or exhaust to or from the building

name: Supply_Air_Plenum
definitions: A component of the HVAC the receives air from the air handling unit to distribute to the building

name: Underfloor_Air_Plenum
definitions: An open space between a structural concrete slab and the underside of a raised access floor system that connects to an air handling unit to receive conditioned and/or ventilating air before delivery to the room(s)

name: Boiler
definitions: A closed, pressure vessel that uses fuel or electricity for heating water or other fluids to supply steam or hot water for heating, humidification, or other applications.

name: Electric_Boiler
definitions: A closed, pressure vessel that uses electricity for heating water or other fluids to supply steam or hot water for heating, humidification, or other applications.

name: Natural_Gas_Boiler
definitions: A closed, pressure vessel that uses natural gas for heating water or other fluids to supply steam or hot water for heating, humidification, or other applications.

name: Condensing_Natural_Gas_Boiler
definitions: A closed, pressure vessel that uses natural gas and heat exchanger that capture and reuse any latent heat for heating water or other fluids to supply steam or hot water for heating, humidification, or other applications.

name: Noncondensing_Natural_Gas_Boiler
definitions: A closed, pressure vessel that uses natural gas with no system to capture latent heat for heating water or other fluids to supply steam or hot water for heating, humidification, or other applications.

name: CRAC
definitions: A device that monitors and maintains the temperature, air distribution and humidity in a network room or data center.

name: Standby_CRAC
definitions: A CRAC that is activated as part of a lead/lag operation or when an alarm occurs in a primary unit

name: Chiller
definitions: Refrigerating machine used to transfer heat between fluids. Chillers are either direct expansion with a compressor or absorption type.

name: Absorption_Chiller
definitions: A chiller that utilizes a thermal or/and chemical process to produce the refrigeration effect necessary to provide chilled water. There is no mechanical compression of the refrigerant taking place within the machine, as occurs within more traditional vapor compression type chillers.

name: Centrifugal_Chiller
definitions: A chiller that uses the vapor compression cycle to chill water. It throws off the heat collected from the chilled water plus the heat from the compressor to a water loop

name: Compressor
definitions: (1) device for mechanically increasing the pressure of a gas. (2) often described as being either open, hermetic, or semihermetic to describe how the compressor and motor drive is situated in relation to the gas or vapor being compressed. Types include centrifugal, axial flow, reciprocating, rotary screw, rotary vane, scroll, or diaphragm. 1. device for mechanically increasing the pressure of a gas. 2. specific machine, with or without accessories, for compressing refrigerant vapor.

name: Computer_Room_Air_Conditioning
definitions: A device that monitors and maintains the temperature, air distribution and humidity in a network room or data center.

name: Condenser
definitions: A heat exchanger in which the primary heat transfer vapor changes its state to a liquid phase.

name: Cooling_Tower
definitions: A cooling tower is a heat rejection device that rejects waste heat to the atmosphere through the cooling of a water stream to a lower temperature. Cooling towers may either use the evaporation of water to remove process heat and cool the working fluid to near the wet-bulb air temperature or, in the case of closed circuit dry cooling towers, rely solely on air to cool the working fluid to near the dry-bulb air temperature.

name: Damper
definitions: Element inserted into an air-distribution system or element of an air-distribution system permitting modification of the air resistance of the system and consequently changing the airflow rate or shutting off the airflow.

name: Economizer_Damper
definitions: A damper that is part of an economizer that is used to module the flow of air

name: Exhaust_Damper
definitions: A damper that modulates the flow of exhaust air

name: Mixed_Damper
definitions: A damper that modulates the flow of the mixed outside and return air streams

name: Outside_Damper
definitions: A damper that modulates the flow of outside air

name: Return_Damper
definitions: A damper that modulates the flow of return air

name: Economizer
definitions: Device that, on proper variable sensing, initiates control signals or actions to conserve energy. A control system that reduces the mechanical heating and cooling requirement.

name: Fan
definitions: Any device with two or more blades or vanes attached to a rotating shaft used to produce an airflow for the purpose of comfort, ventilation, exhaust, heating, cooling, or any other gaseous transport.

name: Booster_Fan
definitions: Fan activated to increase airflow beyond what is provided by the default configuration

name: Ceiling_Fan
definitions: A fan installed on the ceiling of a room for the purpose of air circulation

name: Cooling_Tower_Fan
definitions: A fan that pulls air through a cooling tower and across the louvers where the water falls to aid in heat exchange by the process of evaporation

name: Discharge_Fan
definitions: Fan moving air discharged from HVAC vents
Fan moving supply air -- air that is supplied from the HVAC system into the building

name: Exhaust_Fan
definitions: Fan moving exhaust air -- air that must be removed from a space due to contaminants

name: Fresh_Air_Fan
definitions: Fan moving fresh air -- air that is supplied into the building from the outdoors

name: Return_Fan
definitions: Fan moving return air -- air that is circulated from the building back into the HVAC system

name: Standby_Fan
definitions: Fan that is activated as part of a lead/lag operation or when a primary fan raises an alarm

name: Supply_Fan
definitions: Fan moving supply air -- air that is supplied from the HVAC system into the building
Fan moving air discharged from HVAC vents

name: Filter
definitions: Device to remove gases from a mixture of gases or to remove solid material from a fluid

name: Final_Filter
definitions: The last, high-efficiency filter installed in a sequence to remove the finest particulates from the substance being filtered

name: Intake_Air_Filter
definitions: Filters air intake

name: Mixed_Air_Filter
definitions: A filter that is applied to the mixture of recirculated and outside air

name: Pre_Filter
definitions: A filter installed in front of a more efficient filter to extend the life of the more expensive higher efficiency filter

name: Return_Air_Filter
definitions: Filters return air

name: Fume_Hood
definitions: A fume-collection device mounted over a work space, table, or shelf and serving to conduct unwanted gases away from the area enclosed.

name: HX
definitions: See Heat_Exchanger

A heat exchanger is a piece of equipment built for efficient heat transfer from one medium to another. The media may be separated by a solid wall to prevent mixing or they may be in direct contact (BEDES)

name: Heat_Exchanger
definitions: A heat exchanger is a piece of equipment built for efficient heat transfer from one medium to another. The media may be separated by a solid wall to prevent mixing or they may be in direct contact (BEDES)
See Heat_Exchanger

name: Coil
definitions: Cooling or heating element made of pipe or tube that may or may not be finned and formed into helical or serpentine shape (ASHRAE Dictionary)

name: Cooling_Coil
definitions: A cooling element made of pipe or tube that removes heat from equipment, machines or airflows. Typically filled with either refrigerant or cold water.

name: Chilled_Water_Coil
definitions: A cooling element made of pipe or tube that removes heat from equipment, machines or airflows that is filled with chilled water.

name: Heating_Coil
definitions: A heating element typically made of pipe, tube or wire that emits heat. Typically filled with hot water, or, in the case of wire, uses electricity.

name: Hot_Water_Coil
definitions: A heating element typically made of pipe, tube or wire that emits heat that is filled with hot water.

name: Condenser_Heat_Exchanger
definitions: A heat exchanger in which the primary heat transfer vapor changes its state to a liquid phase.

name: Heat_Wheel
definitions: A rotary heat exchanger positioned within the supply and exhaust air streams of an air handling system in order to recover heat energy

name: Humidifier
definitions: A device that adds moisture to air or other gases

name: Pump
definitions: Machine for imparting energy to a fluid, causing it to do work, drawing a fluid into itself through an entrance port, and forcing the fluid out through an exhaust port.

name: Water_Pump
definitions: A pump that performs work on water

name: Chilled_Water_Pump
definitions: A pump that performs work on chilled water; typically part of a chilled water system

name: Condenser_Water_Pump
definitions: A pump that is part of a condenser system; the pump circulates condenser water from the chiller back to the cooling tower

name: Hot_Water_Pump
definitions: A pump that performs work on hot water; typically part of a hot water system

name: Space_Heater
definitions: A heater used to warm the air in an enclosed area, such as a room or office

name: Terminal_Unit
definitions: A device that regulates the volumetric flow rate and/or the temperature of the controlled medium.

name: Air_Diffuser
definitions: A device that is a component of the air distribution system that controls the delivery of conditioned and/or ventilating air into a room

name: Displacement_Flow_Air_Diffuser
definitions: An air diffuser that is designed for low discharge air speeds to minimize turbulence and induction of room air. This diffuser is used with displacement ventilation systems.

name: Jet_Nozzle_Air_Diffuser
definitions: An air diffuser that is designed to produce high velocity discharge air stream to throw the air over a large distance or target the air stream to a localize area

name: Laminar_Flow_Air_Diffuser
definitions: An air diffuser that is designed for low discharge air speeds to provide uniform and unidirectional air pattern which minimizes room air entrainment

name: CAV
definitions: A terminal unit for which supply air flow rate is constant and the supply air temperature is varied to meet thermal load

name: Constant_Air_Volume_Box
definitions: A terminal unit for which supply air flow rate is constant and the supply air temperature is varied to meet thermal load

name: FCU
definitions: See Fan_Coil_Unit
Terminal device consisting of a heating and/or cooling heat exchanger or 'coil' and fan that is used to control the temperature in the space where it is installed

name: Fan_Coil_Unit
definitions: Terminal device consisting of a heating and/or cooling heat exchanger or 'coil' and fan that is used to control the temperature in the space where it is installed
See Fan_Coil_Unit

name: Radiant_Panel
definitions: A temperature-controlled surface that provides fifty percent (50%) or more of the design heat transfer by thermal radiation.

name: ESS_Panel
definitions: See Embedded_Surface_System_Panel
Radiant panel heating and cooling system where the energy heat source or sink is embedded in a radiant layer which is thermally insulated from the building structure.

name: Embedded_Surface_System_Panel
definitions: Radiant panel heating and cooling system where the energy heat source or sink is embedded in a radiant layer which is thermally insulated from the building structure.
See Embedded_Surface_System_Panel

name: RC_Panel
definitions: See Radiant_Ceiling_Panel
Radiant panel heating and cooling system that are usually made from metal and suspended under the ceiling or insulated from the building structure.

name: Radiant_Ceiling_Panel
definitions: Radiant panel heating and cooling system that are usually made from metal and suspended under the ceiling or insulated from the building structure.
See Radiant_Ceiling_Panel

name: TABS_Panel
definitions: See Thermally_Activated_Building_System_Panel
Radiant panel heating and cooling system where the energy heat source or sink is embedded in the building structure such as in slabs and walls.

name: Thermally_Activated_Building_System_Panel
definitions: Radiant panel heating and cooling system where the energy heat source or sink is embedded in the building structure such as in slabs and walls.
See Thermally_Activated_Building_System_Panel

name: Radiator
definitions: Heat exchangers designed to transfer thermal energy from one medium to another

name: Baseboard_Radiator
definitions: Steam, hydronic, or electric heating device located at or near the floor.

name: Electric_Baseboard_Radiator
definitions: Electric heating device located at or near the floor

name: Hot_Water_Baseboard_Radiator
definitions: Hydronic heating device located at or near the floor

name: Steam_Baseboard_Radiator
definitions: Steam heating device located at or near the floor

name: Electric_Radiator
definitions: Electric heating device

name: Electric_Baseboard_Radiator
definitions: Electric heating device located at or near the floor

name: Hot_Water_Radiator
definitions: Radiator that uses hot water

name: Hot_Water_Baseboard_Radiator
definitions: Hydronic heating device located at or near the floor

name: Steam_Radiator
definitions: Radiator that uses steam

name: Steam_Baseboard_Radiator
definitions: Steam heating device located at or near the floor

name: VAV
definitions: See Variable_Air_Volume_Box
A device that regulates the volume and temperature of air delivered to a zone by opening or closing a damper

name: Variable_Air_Volume_Box
definitions: A device that regulates the volume and temperature of air delivered to a zone by opening or closing a damper
See Variable_Air_Volume_Box

name: RVAV
definitions: See Variable_Air_Volume_Box_With_Reheat
A VAV box with a reheat coil mounted on the discharge end of the unit that can heat the air delivered to a zone

name: Variable_Air_Volume_Box_With_Reheat
generatedLabel: Variable Air Volume Box With Reheat
definitions: A VAV box with a reheat coil mounted on the discharge end of the unit that can heat the air delivered to a zone
See Variable_Air_Volume_Box_With_Reheat

name: Thermostat
definitions: An automatic control device used to maintain temperature at a fixed or adjustable setpoint.

name: Valve
definitions: A device that regulates, directs or controls the flow of a fluid by opening, closing or partially obstructing various passageways

name: Bypass_Valve
definitions: A type of valve installed in a bypass pipeline

name: Condenser_Water_Bypass_Valve
definitions: A valve installed in a bypass line of a condenser water loop

name: Differential_Pressure_Bypass_Valve
definitions: A 2-way, self contained proportional valve with an integral differential pressure adjustment setting.

name: Cooling_Valve
definitions: A valve that controls air temperature by modulating the amount of cold water flowing through a cooling coil

name: Heating_Valve
definitions: A valve that controls air temperature by modulating the amount of hot water flowing through a heating coil

name: Hot_Water_Valve
definitions: A valve regulating the flow of hot water

name: Domestic_Hot_Water_Valve
definitions: A valve regulating the flow of domestic hot water

name: Reheat_Valve
definitions: A valve that controls air temperature by modulating the amount of hot water flowing through a reheat coil

name: Return_Heating_Valve
definitions: A valve installed on the return side of a heat exchanger

name: Isolation_Valve
definitions: A valve that stops the flow of a fluid, usually for maintenance or safety purposes

name: Condenser_Water_Isolation_Valve
definitions: An isolation valve installed in the condenser water loop

name: Water_Valve
definitions: A valve that modulates the flow of water

name: Chilled_Water_Valve
definitions: A valve that modulates the flow of chilled water

name: Condenser_Water_Valve
definitions: A valve that modulates the flow of condenser water

name: Hot_Water_Valve
definitions: A valve regulating the flow of hot water

name: Makeup_Water_Valve
definitions: A valve regulating the flow of makeup water into a water holding tank, e.g. a cooling tower, hot water tank

name: Interface
definitions: A device that provides an occupant control over a lighting system

name: Switch
definitions: A switch used to operate all or part of a lighting installation

name: Dimmer
definitions: A switch providing continuous control over all or part of a lighting installation; typically potentiometer-based

name: Touchpanel
definitions: A switch used to operate all or part of a lighting installation that uses a touch-based mechanism (typically resistive or capacitive) rather than a mechanical actuator

name: Luminaire
definitions: A complete lighting unit consisting of a lamp or lamps and ballast(s) (when applicable) together with the parts designed to distribute the light, to position and protect the lamps, and to connect the lamps to the power supply.

name: Luminaire_Driver
definitions: A power source for a luminaire

name: Louver
definitions: Device consisting of an assembly of parallel sloping vanes, intended to permit the passage of air while providing a measure of protection against environmental influences

name: Meter
definitions: A device that measure usage or consumption of some media --- typically a form energy or power.

name: Building_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures usage or consumption of some media for a whole building

name: Building_Chilled_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of chilled water of a whole building

name: Building_Electrical_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of electricity of a whole building

name: Building_Gas_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of gas of a whole building

name: Building_Hot_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of hot water of a whole building

name: Building_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of water of a whole building

name: Electrical_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of electricity

name: Building_Electrical_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of electricity of a whole building

name: Gas_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of gas

name: Building_Gas_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of gas of a whole building

name: Thermal_Power_Meter
definitions: A standalone thermal power meter

name: Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of water

name: Building_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of water of a whole building

name: Chilled_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of chilled water

name: Building_Chilled_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of chilled water of a whole building

name: Hot_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of hot water

name: Building_Hot_Water_Meter
definitions: A meter that measures the usage or consumption of hot water of a whole building

name: Motor
definitions: A machine in which power is applied to do work by the conversion of various forms of energy into mechanical force and motion.

name: VFD
definitions: Electronic device that varies its output frequency to vary the rotating speed of a motor, given a fixed input frequency. Used with fans or pumps to vary the flow in the system as a function of a maintained pressure.

name: Fan_VFD
definitions: Variable-frequency drive for fans

name: Heat_Wheel_VFD
definitions: A VFD that drives a heat wheel

name: Pump_VFD
definitions: Variable-frequency drive for pumps

name: Variable_Frequency_Drive
definitions: Electronic device that varies its output frequency to vary the rotating speed of a motor, given a fixed input frequency. Used with fans or pumps to vary the flow in the system as a function of a maintained pressure.

name: PV_Panel
definitions: An integrated assembly of interconnected photovoltaic cells designed to deliver a selected level of working voltage and current at its output terminals packaged for protection against environment degradation and suited for incorporation in photovoltaic power systems.

name: PVT_Panel
definitions: A type of solar panels that convert solar radiation into usable thermal and electrical energy

name: Solar_Thermal_Collector
definitions: A type of solar panels that converts solar radiation into thermal energy.

name: PVT_Panel
definitions: A type of solar panels that convert solar radiation into usable thermal and electrical energy

name: Steam_Distribution
definitions: Utilize a steam distribution source to represent how steam is distributed across multiple destinations

name: Water_Distribution
definitions: Utilize a water distribution source to represent how water is distributed across multiple destinations (pipes)

name: Water_Heater
definitions: An apparatus for heating and usually storing hot water

name: Boiler
